By Martha Nuhu Jos –  The Nigerian Film Corporation (NFC) has hailed the appointment of Prof. Ibrahim Gambari as Chief of Staff to Pesident Muhammadu Buhari, describing him as the right man for the job. The Managing Director of NFC, Dr Chidia Maduekwe said this in a statement on Saturday in Jos. Maduekwe, who extolled Gambari’s public and private service record to the nation, said he was needed when the country was in pursuit of effective governance Maduekwe said Gambari’s wealth of experience and the president’s commitment to good governance would see to the development of the country. (NAN) By Stanley Nwanosike Enugu - Igwe Lawrence Agubuzu, Chairman of Enugu State Council of Traditional Rulers’ Council, says Prof. Ibrahim Gambari will bring his `three-fold experiences’ to assist the President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration. Agubuzu stated this in a congratulatory message issued in Enugu on Thursday and made available to the… May 14, 2020 In "Politics" By Ayo Akanni ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - Special Adviser to the President on Niger Delta and Coordinator, Presidential Amnesty Programme, Prof. Charles Dokubo, at the weekend, expressed optimism that training in the film industry will open a vista of opportunities for beneficiaries of the programme. He said the Amnesty Office… June 25, 2018 In "Entertainment" By Martha Agas Jos - National Film Institute  (NFI) is partnering Goethe University, Frankfurt, Germany, to run a master’s degree programmes in film archiving, an official has said. In a statement in Jos on Tuesday, Mr Brian Etuk, the Head of Public and Intergovernmental Affairs, Nigerian Film Corporation (NFC), said… April 2, 2019 In "Entertainment"